# @SHBMV06P516A_BEG_WASMR حدثنا @TR1_ASMR@ عبد الرحيم بن سليمان عن محمد بن إسحاق عن الزهري ومحمد بن علي عن يزيد بن هرمز أن نجدة كتب إلى ابن عباس يسأله عن سهم ذوي القربى لمن هو فكتب كتبت تسألني عن سهم ذوي القربى لمن هو فهو لنا قال إن عمر بن الخطاب دعانا إلى أن ننكح منه أيمنا ونخدم منه عائلنا ونقضي منه عن غارمنا فأبينا ذلك إلا أن يسلمه لنا جميعا فأبى أن يفعل فتركناه عليه. @SHBMV06P516A_END_WASMR
PageV06P516
# @COMMENT: This passage is not found in HNSX. A similar passage is found in WHAYA and WASMR. The fragment describes how Najdah al-Ḥarūrī wrote Ibn ʿAbbās about inheritance rules.

# @IHMAV11P291A_BEG_WASMR وروينا من طريق أبي بكر بن أبي شيبة نا @TR1_ASMR@ عبد الرحمن بن سليمان عن محمد بن إسحاق عن أبي جعفر محمد بن علي بن الحسين أن علي بن أبي طالب كان إذا وجد القتيل بين قريتين قاس ما بينهما. @IHMAV11P291A_END_WASMR
PageV11P291

# @THSHV02P126A_BEG_WASMR
VAR_ZYMXV01P262A VAR_DRQSV05P065A VAR_BQSXV07P585A حدثنا إسحاق بن إبراهيم بن يونس البغدادي أبو يعقوب حدثنا الوليد بن شجاع أبو همام حدثنا @TR1_ASMR@ عبد الرحيم بن سليمان حدثنا محمد بن إسحاق عن ثور بن يزيد عن محمد بن عبيد قال بعثني عدي بن عدي الكندي إلى صفية بنت شيبة أسألها عن أشياء كانت ترويها عن عائشة فقالت حدثتني عائشة أنها سمعت رسول الله صلى الله عليه وسلم يقول لا عتاق ولا طلاق في إغلاق PageV02P126  وذكر البخاري هذا الحديث عن أحمد بن حنبل عن @TR2_SAII@ سعد بن PageV02P127 إبراهيم بن سعد عن @TR1_SACD@ أبيه عن ابن إسحاق عن ثور بن يزيد الكلاعي عن محمد بن عبيد بن أبي صالح المكي. @THSHV02P126A_END_WASMR
PageV02P128
# @COMMENT: Passage not found in HSNX. The tradition is set during the ḥajj when ʿAdī b. ʿAdī al-Kindī advised Muḥammad b. ʿUbayd b. Abī Ṣāliḥ al-Makkī to go collect a tradition from Ṣafīyah bint Shaybah b. ʿUthmān b. Abī Ṭalḥah. Muḥammad b. ʿUbayd b. Abī Ṣāliḥ and ʿAdī b. ʿAdī al-Kindī are not mentioned in HSNX. Ṣafīyah bint Shaybah b. ʿUthmān is mentioned in HSNXV02P411C regarding the Conquest of Mecca (also see via WSACD NYMXV06P3378A). Thawr b. Yazīd al-Kalāʿī, Abū Khālid, is mentioned three times by WZATB (HSNXV01P166A, HSNXV01P308A, and HSNXV01P634C). According to Muḥammad b. Saʿd, he was from the people of Ḥimṣ and died in Jerusalem in 153/770 at the age of 60. His grandfather fought for Muʿāwiyah at Ṣiffīn against ʿAlī (TKXXV07P324A). Muḥammad b. ʿUbayd b. Abī Ṣāliḥ al-Makkī is mentioned in BKHBV01P171C, HJKXV01P583A, BNTHV07P371C, and MZTXV19P215A only in relation to this tradition, although the latter source states that he also related from Mujāhid b. Jabr al-Makkī and in addition to Thawr b. Yazīd al-Ḥimṣī, he also related to Mujāhid b. Jabr al-Makkī. According to HJRBV09P330A he lived in Jerusalem. No date of death is mentioned. ʿAdī b. ʿAdī b. ʿUmayrah al-Kindī al-Shaybānī, Abū Farwah al-Jazīrī, was a member of the al-Ḥārith b. Muʿāwiyah b. Thawr tribe. Described as pious by al-Ṭabarī, he commanded troops under Muḥammad b. Marwān against Khārijī rebels in 76/ 695 (TBRBV06P243A). He is described as a partisan of the Umayyads and was appointed as commander of Mūsil, the Jazīrah, and then Armīnīyah by ʿUmar b. ʿAbd al-ʿAzīz (TDSHV40P137A, although MZTXV19P5354B states this was done by Sulaymān b. ʿAbd al-Mālik). He was included among the 3rd generation of successors in the Jazīrah and to have been trustworthy (ibid., 138). He died in 120/738 according to al-Dhahabī and others (DHBRV01P116D). Ṣafīyah bint Shaybah b. ʿUthmān b. Abī Ṭalḥah was a Meccan companion and related from many of the Prophet's wives and related to many in the first generation of successors. No date of death is mentioned (see, MZTXV35P212B). One of the most comonly quoted traditions in the Ibn Isḥāq corpus. Passage also found in WAANH, WZAZA, and WSACD. Unable to place the date of the event in which the tradition was collected in Mecca. Most likely to be placed in the opinions of Muḥammad in fiqh section. @EC_12/16/22@

